---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About — Scott Clark"
  description="Bio, experience, education, and skills for Scott Clark. CEO of Distributional, former co-founder/CEO of SigOpt (acquired by Intel), Cornell PhD, Forbes 30 Under 30."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">About Me</h1>
    <p class="mb-12 text-xl text-text-secondary">
      CEO &amp; Co-Founder of Distributional. Building reliable AI for the enterprise.
    </p>

    <!-- Bio -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        I'm an expert in machine learning, Bayesian optimization, and AI observability. I've spent my career
        applying optimal learning techniques across bioinformatics, production advertising systems, and
        enterprise AI testing. I'm driven by the belief that AI systems should be trustworthy and reliable
        before they're deployed in the real world.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        I'm currently building <a href="https://www.distributional.com" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent transition-colors">Distributional</a>,
        a modern platform for enterprise AI testing and evaluation. Before that, I co-founded
        <a href="https://sigopt.com" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent transition-colors">SigOpt</a>,
        an intelligent experimentation platform that was acquired by Intel in 2020. At Intel, I led a 200-person
        AI and HPC software engineering team focused on supercomputer applications.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        I hold a Ph.D. in Applied Mathematics and an M.S. in Computer Science from Cornell University, where
        I was a Department of Energy Computational Science Graduate Fellow. My research focused on parallel
        machine learning algorithms for bioinformatics and global optimization. I also created the open-source
        <a href="https://github.com/Yelp/MOE" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent transition-colors">Metric Optimization Engine (MOE)</a>
        at Yelp, one of the first production Bayesian optimization systems.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Awards -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Awards &amp; Honors</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-lg border border-surface-lighter bg-surface-light/50 p-4">
          <span class="mt-0.5 rounded bg-accent/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold text-accent-light">2016</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold">Forbes 30 Under 30</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Enterprise Technology category</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-lg border border-surface-lighter bg-surface-light/50 p-4">
          <span class="mt-0.5 rounded bg-accent/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold text-accent-light">2016</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold">College of Science Young Alumni Award</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Oregon State University</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-lg border border-surface-lighter bg-surface-light/50 p-4">
          <span class="mt-0.5 rounded bg-accent/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-sm font-bold text-accent-light">2008</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold">DOE Computational Science Graduate Fellowship</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Full 4-year scholarship (~$300,000), Department of Energy</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Experience -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Experience</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent/30 pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2023 — Present</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Co-Founder &amp; CEO</h3>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-text-muted">Distributional</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Founded Distributional with an 11-person founding team from Bloomberg, Google, Meta, Intel, SigOpt,
            Slack, Stripe, Uber, and Yelp. Building a modern platform for enterprise AI testing and evaluation
            to make AI safe, reliable, and secure. Raised $30M from Andreessen Horowitz, Two Sigma Ventures,
            Point72 Ventures, SV Angel, and 40+ angel investors.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2020 — 2023</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">VP / General Manager, AI &amp; HPC Software</h3>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-text-muted">Intel Corporation</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Led a 200-person AI and high-performance computing software engineering team focused on
            supercomputer applications following Intel's acquisition of SigOpt.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2014 — 2020</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Co-Founder &amp; CEO</h3>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-text-muted">SigOpt (YC W15, acquired by Intel)</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Built an intelligent experimentation platform that accelerates and amplifies the impact of modelers
            everywhere. Raised over $17M from Andreessen Horowitz, Intel, and other investors. Grew the team
            and product from inception to acquisition by Intel in November 2020.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2012 — 2014</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Data Mining Engineer &amp; Lead, Ad Targeting</h3>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-text-muted">Yelp</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Developed and open-sourced MOE (Metric Optimization Engine), a Bayesian optimization framework.
            Implemented multi-armed bandit strategies for ad selection. Led cross-organization teams and
            directed the Yelp Dataset Challenge.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2008 — 2012</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Research Fellow (DOE CSGF)</h3>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-text-muted">Cornell University / DOE National Laboratories</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Practicum research at Lawrence Berkeley National Lab (genome validation software) and
            Los Alamos National Lab (parallel alignment algorithm development). Earlier research at
            Max Planck Institute for Physics of Complex Systems and UC Davis.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Volunteer -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Volunteer &amp; Advisory</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2022 — 2025</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Board of Trustees Member</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">OMSI (Oregon Museum of Science and Industry)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Advisory Roles</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Oregon State University College of Science</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Education -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Education</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent/30 pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2008 — 2012</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">Ph.D. in Applied Mathematics</h3>
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm text-text-muted">Cornell University, Ithaca, NY</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            M.S. in Computer Science (2011). DOE Computational Science Graduate Fellowship.
            Advisor: Peter Frazier. Thesis: "Parallel Machine Learning Algorithms in Bioinformatics
            and Global Optimization."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-surface-lighter pl-6">
          <div class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-light">2004 — 2008</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-bold">B.Sc. Mathematics, B.Sc. Computational Physics, B.Sc. Physics</h3>
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm text-text-muted">Oregon State University, Corvallis, OR</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            Graduated Magna Cum Laude with three bachelor's degrees. Minors in Actuarial Sciences
            and Mathematical Sciences.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Skills -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Skills</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {[
          "Machine Learning", "Bayesian Optimization", "AI Testing & Observability",
          "Python", "C/C++", "CUDA", "TypeScript",
          "Distributed Systems", "Parallel Computing", "Data Mining",
          "Bioinformatics", "Global Optimization", "Gaussian Processes",
          "A/B Testing", "Experiment Design",
          "AWS", "MapReduce", "Linux",
        ].map((skill) => (
          <span class="rounded-full border border-surface-lighter bg-surface-light px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-text-secondary">
            {skill}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resume Download -->
    <section>
      <a
        href="/resume/scott-clark-resume.pdf"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-accent px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-lg shadow-accent/25 transition-all hover:bg-accent-light hover:shadow-accent-light/25"
      >
        Download Resume (PDF)
      </a>
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
